{{Infobox journal | title = Intercultural Pragmatics | cover = Intercultural Pragmatics.gif | editor = [[István Kecskés (linguist)|István Kecskés]] | discipline = [[Pragmatics]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | former_names = | abbreviation = | publisher = [[Mouton de Gruyter]] | country = Germany | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2004–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.degruyter.de/journals/intcultpragm/detailEn.cfm | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 57359121 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1612-295X | eISSN = 1613-365X | boxwidth = }}
'''''Intercultural Pragmatics''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published quarterly by [[Mouton de Gruyter]]. It covers both theoretical and practical aspects of [[pragmatics]] in an intercultural context, aiming at promoting discussion among researchers within different disciplines, such as theoretical and applied linguistics, psychology and [[communication studies]].<ref name="description">{{cite web | url=http://www.degruyter.de/journals/intcultpragm/detailEn.cfm | title=Intercultural Pragmatics - Aims & Scope | accessdate=2011-01-09 | publisher=Walter de Gruyter}}</ref>
The journal was established in 2004. The current [[editor-in-chief]] is [[István Kecskés (linguist)|István Kecskés]] ([[University at Albany, SUNY]]).
