{{Infobox Criminal organization | name = Zoe Pound | image = | caption = | founded = | founding location = [[Miami, Florida]]<ref name=FBI/> | years active = | territory = Miami, Florida;<ref name=FBI/>[[Key West, Florida]]<ref>{{cite news |publisher=Hispanically Speaking News |date=25 February 2011 |url=http://www.hispanicallyspeakingnews.com/notitas-de-noticias/details/ice-operation-in-south-florida-net-24-criminal-aliens/5606/ |title=ICE Operation in South Florida Net 24 Criminal Aliens |accessdate=26 February 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110302142106/http://www.hispanicallyspeakingnews.com/notitas-de-noticias/details/ice-operation-in-south-florida-net-24-criminal-aliens/5606/ |archive-date=2 March 2011 |dead-url=no |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Fort Pierce, Florida]]<ref name=ftpierce/> | ethnicity = [[Haiti]]an<ref name=FBI/> | membership est = | criminal activities = Drug trafficking, Robbery,<ref name=FBI/> Racketeering<ref name= ftpierce/> | allies = | rivals = }}
'''Zoe Pound''' is a criminal [[street gang]] based in [[Miami, Florida]] founded by [[Haitians|Haitian]] immigrants in the Mid 1990s.<ref name=FBI>{{cite web |publisher=Federal Bureau of Investigation |location=Indianapolis |date=4 February 2010 |url=http://indianapolis.fbi.gov/dojpressrel/pressrel10/ip020410.htm |title=Twenty-Two Charged Federally in Evansville Drug Trafficking Case |accessdate=20 February 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100817115452/http://indianapolis.fbi.gov/dojpressrel/pressrel10/ip020410.htm |archive-date=17 August 2010 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
==Etymology== ''Zoe'' is the anglicized variant of the word ''Zo'', which is [[Haitian Creole]] to mean ''bone,'' whose members were known to be "hard to the bone." When conflicts against Haitians arose, the ''pound'' would be sought out to retaliate, thus the street gang name, ''Zoe Pound'' came to be.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j12DHZyxewAC&pg=PA169&lpg=PA169&dq=zoe+pound+means&source=bl&ots=SuLDYfoRWi&sig=fuLnboK0dOYrrByUXpBzIwJIE_I&hl=en&sa=X&ei=maIrVODFIImryASMzoGQCw&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAjge#v=onepage&q=zoe%20pound%20means&f=false |title=Magic City: Trials of a Native Son |author1=Daddy, Trick |author2=Bailey, Peter |page=169 |isbn=978-1-4391-4852-5 |accessdate=1 October 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312131837/https://books.google.com/books?id=j12DHZyxewAC&pg=PA169&lpg=PA169&dq=zoe+pound+means&source=bl&ots=SuLDYfoRWi&sig=fuLnboK0dOYrrByUXpBzIwJIE_I&hl=en&sa=X&ei=maIrVODFIImryASMzoGQCw&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAjge#v=onepage&q=zoe%20pound%20means&f=false |archive-date=12 March 2017 |dead-url=no |df=dmy-all }}</ref> ==History== Having branched out from Miami in the two decades leading up to 2010, they are known to be involved in drug trafficking and robbery and related violent crimes in support of their drug trafficking activities in [[Evansville, Indiana]].<ref name=FBI/>
In 2004, six Zoe Pound leaders were arrested on [[racketeering]] and conspiracy charges in [[Fort Pierce, Florida]] after [[Florida Department of Law Enforcement]] offices convinced several gang members to [[Turn state's evidence|give testimony for the prosecution]].<ref name=ftpierce>{{cite web |last=Greenlee |first=Will |date=18 June 2009 |publisher=TCPalm |url=http://www.tcpalm.com/news/2009/jun/18/six-alleged-leaders-of-fort-pierce-gang-facing/ |title=Six alleged leaders of Fort Pierce gang facing charges |accessdate=26 February 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716194638/http://www.tcpalm.com/news/2009/jun/18/six-alleged-leaders-of-fort-pierce-gang-facing/ |archive-date=16 July 2011 |dead-url=no |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
